cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use BioSentinel in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "BioSentinel: AI-Powered Longitudinal Health Monitoring and Early Disease Detection"
version: 2.3.3
date-released: "2026-03-19"
url: "https://github.com/liveupx/biosentinel"
repository-code: "https://github.com/liveupx/biosentinel"
license: MIT
abstract: >
  BioSentinel is an open-source platform for longitudinal health monitoring and 
  early disease detection using machine learning. It tracks biomarker trajectories 
  over time across four disease domains (cancer, metabolic, cardiovascular, hematologic)
  using Gradient Boosting models with SHAP explainability. Version 2.3 adds Claude AI 
  integration for vision-based lab report extraction, plain-English clinical narratives,
  and longitudinal anomaly detection.
keywords:
  - longitudinal-health
  - early-disease-detection
  - machine-learning
  - clinical-decision-support
  - biomarkers
  - electronic-health-records
  - explainable-ai
  - SHAP
  - FastAPI
  - open-source-healthcare
